[
    {
        "content": "<p>What’s the simplest way to state the proposition that Type 0 contains a universe?</p>",
        "id": 526110700,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1751038945
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What does that mean?</p>",
        "id": 526112799,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1751039761
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess you could state that it forms an inaccessible cardinal</p>",
        "id": 526112925,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1751039810
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah probably</p>",
        "id": 526119194,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1751042132
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>is it possible to prove that the cardinality of Type 0 is inaccessible? the cardinality of Type u is notoriously hard to pin down... in fact I think the exact value may be independent of Lean</p>\n<p>you can certainly prove that the cardinality of Type u is greater than or equal to an inaccessible cardinal (specifically <code>Cardinal.univ.{u, u+1}</code>)... maybe that's good enough</p>",
        "id": 526153499,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Diamond",
        "timestamp": 1751059283
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>oh wait, you were just asking about stating it, not proving it... nvm</p>",
        "id": 526154785,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Diamond",
        "timestamp": 1751060157
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm just wondering if there's a convenient way to state it in terms of type theory and basically without much reference to cardinality</p>",
        "id": 526160384,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1751065255
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess I'm not sure what you specifically mean by \"universe\"</p>",
        "id": 526160473,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Diamond",
        "timestamp": 1751065344
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>let's say it's equivalent to |X| being an inaccessible cardinal</p>",
        "id": 526160497,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1751065376
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>well, by that definition, <code>Cardinal</code> would be a universe, as would <code>Ordinal</code></p>",
        "id": 526160614,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Diamond",
        "timestamp": 1751065510
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The only problem is that they don't live in <code>Type 0</code></p>",
        "id": 526160634,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1751065527
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in fact you can't actually prove what i asked</p>",
        "id": 526160643,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1751065534
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>hmm</p>",
        "id": 526160654,
