    {
        "content": "<p>Informal proof: recall that a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inaccessible_cardinal\">strongly inaccessible cardinal is one that is uncountable, regular, and a strong limit cardinal</a>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Uncountable: take the powerset of <code>ℕ</code>.</li>\n<li>Regular: this means its cofinality is itself, which is captured by the union axiom.</li>\n<li>Strong limit cardinal: That's the powerset axiom.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And for the other way round, note how I've used all three axioms in the above proof.</p>",
        "id": 526163082,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1751068011
    },
